  "notes": [
    "Available FALL 2025 - Actuarial Science, B.S. Degree The Actuarial Science major is selective based on GPA and the strength of academic preparation for the major. Students are required to: 1) Complete community college courses equivalent to the following 12-13 lower division UCR Business Administration major requirements listed below. 2) Attain a minimum GPA of 2.70 in all UC transferable course work, and a minimum 2.50 GPA in the eleven lower division major prerequisites listed below. (This GPA is a baseline for consideration and not a guarantee of admission.) 3) Complete IGETC/CalGETC or the UCR breadth pattern for the School of Business UCR Breadth pattern. AP Exam - Satisfy Course Requirement Section Economics: Macroeconomics Exam Minimum score of 3 satisfies ECON 2 Economics: Microeconomics Exam Minimum score of 3 satisfies ECON 3 Mathematics: AB Exam or AB Subscore from BC Exam Minimum score of 3 satisfies MATH 9A or MATH 7A Mathematics: BC Exam Minimum score of 3 satisfies MATH 9A and MATH 9B or MATH 7A and MATH 7B Minimum score of 4 satisfies MATH 9A, MATH 9B, MATH 9C or MATH 7A, MATH 7B, MATH 9C Statistics Exam Minimum score of 4 satisfies STAT 8 or STAT 10 If the sending institution offers honors courses , the articulation for the same course number will be used. For more information regarding this major and UCR's transfer selection process, please visit Actuarial Science . For information about the UC Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) program, please visit Transfer Admission Guarantee ."
